<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: v2.2.7. See <a href="./angband.oook.cz/screen-show.php?id=569">http://angband.oook.cz/screen-show.php?id=569</a>. Searching the in-game help produces ugly-looking (not to mention corrupted) output. <p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: Output was 
<pre>4. Tulkas - Another of Tulkaslar, Tulkas values strengtTulkascourage. 
</pre>
</p>
<p>
The line in gods.txt is 
<pre>4. *****g_tulkas.txt*0[Tulkas] - another of the Valar, Tulkas values strength and courage.
</pre>
</p>
<p>
The code first prints the text interpreting the special commands, then prints the search text in yellow at the position found in the help file, without considering the extra space needed for special help file commands. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: A search for the other gods on the same page produces similar results, though the word is duplicated only once, not twice. A search for Morgoth on that page also produces odd results. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./ZasVid">ZasVid</a></strong>: This doesn't occur so badly with new helpfiles introduced by fearof4s in 2.3.0 CVS. 
</p>
